{{TagLine|AC9600 Wireless Dual Band Gigabit Gaming Router}} :''ASUS ROG Rapture Aura 10G Gaming Router'' :[https://www.asus.com/Gaming-Networking/Gaming-Routers-Products/ Product page] "GT-AC9600 REV3.20" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. :''ASUS ROG Rapture GT-AC9600, ASUS RT-AC9600R'' * [[ASUS GT-AC9600]] (ROG Rapture Aura 10G) - ''AC9600 WiFi Gaming Router'' : FCC ID: [https://fccid.io/MSQ-RTG03H MSQ-RTG03H] (04/28/2017) IC: 3568A-RTG03H, PSU: 19V/3.42A : CPU: Alpine AL5140 @1.7GHz (Quad Core), LAN: [[Aquantia]] [http://www.aquantia.com/products/enterprise/aqr407 AQR107/407] : WLAN: [[Quantenna]] 802.11an/ac (5GHz 8T8R), 1x 802.11bgn (2.4GHz 4T4R) The manufacturer stated in the [https://fccid.io/document.php?id=3373446 FCC test report] is [[Askey]] and Compal. : C2PC on 7/14/17 adds 160MHz BW and DFS.. {{see also|ASUS BRT-AC828/M2|Netgear R9000}} ===Specification=== *[http://www.quantenna.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/QSR10GUV1.1.pdf ''QSR10GU: 8x8 + 4x4 DBDC Wireless LAN Chipset Solution'' on '''Quantenna'''] :Wave 3, 8x8 MU-MIMO 802.11ac {AC9600} :802.11n: 2.4GHz (40MHz) 4T4R 1Gbps :802.11ac: 5GHz (160MHz) 8T8R 8.6Gbps ===Forum threads=== *[https://www.snbforums.com/threads/another-new-router-entry-on-the-fcc-gt-ac9600.38867/ ''Another new router entry on the FCC: GT-AC9600'' on '''SNB''' forums] :- CPU: Alpine AL5140 @1.7GHz (Quad Core ARMv7 Cortex-A15) :- WLAN: [[Quantenna]] QSR10GU 802.11abgn/ac (2.4/5GHz) :- WAN: [[Aquantia]] AQR107 - 1x WAN + 1x LAN (10GbE ports) :- LAN: [[Realtek]] RTL8370MB switch - 8x LAN (1GbE ports) :- LED: RGB/Aura lighting :- SSD: M.2 SSD support *[http://forums.hardwarezone.com.sg/internet-bandwidth-networking-clinic-4/%5Bmaylyn-networking%5D-upcoming-asus-rt-ax88u-asus-gt-ac9600-rog-rapture-aura-10g-gaming-router-5684303.html ''Upcoming ASUS RT-AX88U, ASUS GT-AC9600 ROG Rapture
